article.headline: Fresno St. 73, CS Bakersfield 55
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Tim Steed scored 23 points and Fresno State beat Cal State Bakersfield 73-55 on Wednesday night. Steed was 10 for 16 from the field and grabbed seven rebounds, and Greg Smith had 13 points and eight rebounds for the Bulldogs (12-14). Fresno State trailed 37-34 at halftime, but scored the first 10 points of the second half. The Roadrunners' last lead was 47-46, then Steed made a 3-pointer to put Fresno State ahead for good. Bakersfield was held without a field goal in the final 6 1/2 minutes. The Bulldogs completed a season sweep between the schools, which are less than 100 miles apart. Fresno State won 79-49 at home on Feb. 7. Rashad Savage had 12 points and 16 rebounds for Bakersfield (9-15), which has lost 10 of its last 11 games. Alex Johnson was the Roadrunners' top scorer with 15 points.
